      "content": "Here's the summary of the log entry: \n\nID: CVE-2025-9821\nType: SQL Injection (Unauthenticated)\nEndpoint: /legacy/customer_login.php\nSeverity: CRITICAL\nExploitability: High (Public exploit scripts available)\n\nThe scan is screaming 'Critical'. If we don't patch this, we're looking at a total data breach of the customer DB. But if we take the portal down for the 6-hour patch, the latency penalties and consumer hitting us for the outage will be massive. Give me a straight answer: is this actually a 'drop everything' situation, or can we just monitor it until the weekend? I need to know if I'm overreacting.",
